        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int bt_mesh_rpr_scan_start</definition>
        <argsstring>(struct bt_mesh_rpr_cli *cli, const struct bt_mesh_rpr_node *srv, const uint8_t uuid[16], uint8_t timeout, uint8_t max_devs, struct bt_mesh_rpr_scan_status *status)</argsstring>
        <name>bt_mesh_rpr_scan_start</name>
        <param>
          <type>struct <ref refid="structbt__mesh__rpr__cli" kindref="compound">bt_mesh_rpr_cli</ref> *</type>
          <declname>cli</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const struct <ref refid="structbt__mesh__rpr__node" kindref="compound">bt_mesh_rpr_node</ref> *</type>
          <declname>srv</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="stdint_8h_1a3cb4a16b0e8d6af0af86d4fd6ba5fd9d" kindref="member">uint8_t</ref></type>
          <declname>uuid</declname>
          <array>[16]</array>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="stdint_8h_1a3cb4a16b0e8d6af0af86d4fd6ba5fd9d" kindref="member">uint8_t</ref></type>
          <declname>timeout</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="stdint_8h_1a3cb4a16b0e8d6af0af86d4fd6ba5fd9d" kindref="member">uint8_t</ref></type>
          <declname>max_devs</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>struct <ref refid="structbt__mesh__rpr__scan__status" kindref="compound">bt_mesh_rpr_scan_status</ref> *</type>
          <declname>status</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Start scanning for unprovisioned devices. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Tells the Remote Provisioning Server to start scanning for unprovisioned devices. The Server will report back the results through the <ref refid="structbt__mesh__rpr__cli_1a32b3c63218b506d1bc5759640cb3fb81" kindref="member">bt_mesh_rpr_cli::scan_report</ref> callback.</para>
<para>Use the <computeroutput>uuid</computeroutput> parameter to scan for a specific device, or leave it as NULL to report all unprovisioned devices.</para>
<para>The Server will ignore duplicates, and report up to <computeroutput>max_devs</computeroutput> number of devices. Requesting a <computeroutput>max_devs</computeroutput> number that&apos;s higher than the Server&apos;s capability will result in an error.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>cli</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Remote Provisioning Client. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>srv</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Remote Provisioning Server. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>uuid</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Device UUID to scan for, or NULL to report all devices. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>timeout</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Scan timeout in seconds. Must be at least 1 second. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>max_devs</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Max number of devices to report, or 0 to report as many as possible. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>status</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Scan status response buffer.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>0 on success, or (negative) error code otherwise. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
